text.tspan: Find rAAV integration sites in host DNA genome after
in vivo gene transfert in mice
Adeno associated viral vectors / Long term efficient gene transfert
From wild type viruses to recombinant gene therapy vectors
Successfull gene therapy treatment with rAAV vectors
rAAV integration into host cell genome
Long term rAAV genome persistance and expression
* Low integration frequency in host genomic DNA < 1/10000
* Numerous preclinical studies to evaluate the frequency
* In 2 studies = AAV was associated integration with hepatocellular carcinoma
Looking for a needle in a haystack.
Extract virus/host genome junctions in pair end sequencing data
Junctions could be inside a read or between the 2 mate of a pair
Bad quality sequences may result in unmapped reads or false positive
= Compare the efficiency of several aligner (BWA, BALSA, G-Blast...)
Homology between virus and fragment of host genome may result in false positive junctions.
= Remove virus homologies in host genome (blast and edit)
False junctions are created during NGS library preparation
= de novo assembly of junctions and keep only junction supported by multiple reads
# Values can by customized with users values, but the file template must
# * = Changes of value are not recommended for proper programm execution
# Frequency of mutations in final reads (min = 0, max = 1, FLOAT)
# Allow sampling in repeat regions identified by lowercase characters (BOOLEAN)
# Allow sampling in ambigous IUPAC DNA bases (BOOLEAN)
# Generate graphical output du visualize coverage over junctions and distibution of fragment size if pair mode
# Generate a sampling report for each reference (ie. number of time where a read was randomly sampled)
### Relative frequencies of DNA source in fastq (sum of frequencies should be equal to 1)
### Parameters specific to junctions between host and viral DNA
# Minimal number bases of bases from each references in reads
# Mean number of sampling in true junctions (min = 0, max = freq_tj * read_num, FLOAT)
# Mean number of sampling in false junction (min = 0, max = freq_tj * read_num, FLOAT) *
## Parameters of fragment sonication distribution to set up if paired end mode
# Minimal sonication size (min = read_len + min_chimeric, max = size of reference sequences, INTEGER)
# Minimal sonication size (min = sonic_min, max = size of reference sequences, INTEGER)
# Minimal sonication size (min = sonic_min, max = size of reference sequences, INTEGER)
# Certainty of the sonication smire (min = 5 (wide peak), max = 50 (thin peak), INTEGER) *
# Quality score scale of fastq output file (fastq-sanger OR fastq-solexa OR fastq-illumina) *
# Quality range for mean Phred scores (very-good OR good OR medium OR bad OR very-bad) *
\brief Generates random insertion sites of a given viral DNA in an host DNA and output Fastq Files
\brief Finds virus insertion site in host genomic DNA from pair end NGS data
Isis Output : Fragment lenght distribution (pair end mode only)
Isis Output : Read coverage over junctions
